<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-1378] Provide LRU option for L2 data cache</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-1378</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Default data cache operation when it is full is to randomly toss an entity.  For queries that return &amp;gt;1 entity, this means the most recent query is not guaranteed to be cached in its entirety.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Jeremy provided this code to me which certainly works, and should be integrated into the base data cache support...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) Create a new plugin class:  (bundle it with your test app)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;package test;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;import org.apache.openjpa.datacache.AbstractDataCache;&lt;br/&gt;
import org.apache.openjpa.datacache.ConcurrentDataCache;&lt;br/&gt;
import org.apache.openjpa.util.CacheMap;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public class TomsCache extends ConcurrentDataCache {&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    protected CacheMap newCacheMap() {&lt;br/&gt;
        return new CacheMap(true, 1000) {&lt;br/&gt;
            protected void entryRemoved(Object key, Object value,&lt;br/&gt;
                boolean expired) &lt;/p&gt;
{
                keyRemoved(key, expired);
            }
&lt;p&gt;        };&lt;br/&gt;
    }&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) Enable your plugin using a persistence property.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  &amp;lt;property name=&quot;openjpa.DataCache&quot; value=&quot;test.TomsCache(CacheSize=5, SoftReferenceSize=0)&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The oldest entry should get evicted first.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
